<DocsLayout title={title}>
<h1>progrok proxy</h1>
<p>Start a local OpenAI-compatible proxy that injects your OAuth token into every request.</p>
<pre><code>{`progrok proxy -p 18645`}</code></pre>
<h2>Options</h2>
<p><code>-p, --port</code> — Port to listen on (default: 18645).<br/><code>--host</code> — Bind address (default: 127.0.0.1).</p>
<h2>How it works</h2>
<p>The proxy intercepts outgoing requests and replaces any bearer token in the <code>Authorization</code> header with your current OAuth token, so existing OpenAI-compatible clients work without configuration changes.</p>
</DocsLayout>
